<H2><A NAME="SECTION00054000000000000000">
Membership of Scientific Associations and Advisory Boards</A>
</H2>
 
She is/was a member of the following scientific associations: AACE, 
ACM, AISB, AICA, AI*IA, AAAI, AAR, GULP, EATCS, ALP, IEEE, UMI, FoLLI.

<P>
<UL>
<LI><I>1988</I>  Founder of 
AI*IA, the Italian Association for Artificial Intelligence.

<P>
<LI><I>1988 - 1995</I>  Member of the Board of Directors of AI*IA, the 
Italian Association for Artificial Intelligence.

<P>
<LI><I>1988 - 1991</I>   President of  AI*IA, the Italian Association 
for Artificial Intelligence.

<P>
<LI><I>1989 - 1991</I> Member of the Advisory Board of IJCAI91.

<P>
<LI><I>1991 - Present</I>  Member of the Executive Board of 
COMPUNET, the Network of Excellence in Computational Logic of the 
European Union.

<P>
<LI><I>1995 - 2005</I>  Member of the Board of Trustees of IJCAI, as 
Conference Chairperson for IJCAI99.

<P>
<LI><I>1996</I>  Appointed by VSNU (The Association of Dutch 
Universities) in the Committee for the 5 year evaluation of the quality of the 
research in Computer Science of the  
Departments of Mathematics and Computer Science of the Universities of 
the Netherlands.

<P>
<LI><I>1996 - 1999</I>  Elected Chairperson of IFIP TC12 Technical 
Committee on Artificial Intelligence, resigned after one year.

<P>
<LI><I>1997 - 2001</I>  Member of the 
Advisory Board of Robocup International.

<P>
<LI><I>1999 - 2001</I>  President of the Board of Trustees of IJCAI.

<P>
<LI><I>2003 </I> Member of the Panel for the evaluation of  the quality of the research in Computer Science of the Portuguese Research Centers.

<P>
<LI><I>2004 </I>  President of the Award Committee  of IJCAI.

<P>
</UL>

<P>
She has represented AI*IA within ECCAI.

<P>
She represents AICA within IFIP TC12 - Artificial Intelligence.

<P>
Member of WG 1 of TC2: Knowledge Representation.

<P>
Member of the Board of Directors of the ``Progetto 
Finalizzato Sistemi Informatici e Calcolo Parallelo" of CNR.

<P>
Member of several advisory panels and 
reviewer's panel for the European Union (projects ESPRIT and DELTA).

<P>
